                                         "text":  "### Introduction\n\nBefore we talk about our planet and the divisions we have created, let us explore what we know about how nature formed the structures we recognize today.\n\n#### An interdisciplinary atlas?\n\nYes! The areas of knowledge are interconnected. That is why we include different disciplines to help you better understand how the world works.",
                                         "source":  [

                                                    ],
                                         "date_time":  null,
                                         "isTable":  false,
                                         "imgdesc":  "",
                                         "format":  "markdown",
                                         "PostMention":  ""
                                     },
                                     {
                                         "text":  "#### A Law\n\nIn his classes on the History of Asia, Dr. Abdul Karim Khan presents a fundamental relationship between History and Geography: *\"...if History has any laws, Geography is the first law\"* (<htcite0>). Based on this definition, it becomes essential to study the evolution of the continents and of our species from this perspective.\n\n#### Stages of learning\n\nIn school, we are introduced to subjects such as Science or Geography even before entering university. However, teaching often limits itself to showing only the initial stages of this field. These stages could be called proto-Geography or pre-Geography, as proposed by Dr. Francisco González A. Redondo (<htcite1>; <htcite2>; <htcite3>).</p></p>In the texts of this section, we present the concepts of pre-Geography and proto-Geography, gradually connecting them to Geography through mathematics.",
